<p><img style="float: right;" src="/images/logos/logo.COSI.Function.2022.png" width="100px">The mission of the Function Community of Special Interest (Function-COSI) is to bring together computational biologists, experimental biologists, biocurators, and others who are dealing with the important problem of gene and gene product function prediction, to share ideas and create collaborations.</p>
<button class="btn btn-xs btn-info collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#function_">Read More</button>
<div id="function_" class="collapse">
<p>The Function COSI features the Critical Assessment of Function Annotation, an ongoing community challenge aimed at improving methods for protein function prediction. The Function-COSI holds annual meetings alongside ISMB. Also, we are conducting the multi-year Critical Assessment of protein Function Annotation, or CAFA, experiment.</p>
